title: A Very Holy Place
review: One of the most serene places that I have ever visited. An architectural masterpiece in the making. It is very popular amongst Indian and foreign tourists - known all over the country and in many other lands.

title: Good
review: Known simply as Swami Bagh, this huge white marble mausoleum , which houses the tomb of Sri Shiv Dayal Singh Seth, the founder of the Radhasoami Faith..

title: Swami bagh
review: it is one of the best place to visit in agra. it is also known as swami bagh. this place is very quiet and it was built more than 100 years ago.

title: Beware, stay away.
review: This is a terrible place to go while in Agra, its being run by goons in disguise as security guards, they misbehave with everyone who wants to see this monument.

title: Tomb of Sri Shiv Dayal Singh Seth
review: It's white marble mausoleum dedicated to Sri Shiv Dayal Singh Seth. Very nice floral carving in marbles is worth to look. It was built in memory of the sri Swamiji Maharaj(Sri Shiv Dayal Singh Seth) founder of Radhaswami satsang (A religion which built in principles of Hinduism, Christianity, Buddhism and Sikhism)

title: Good Work!!!
review: Samadhi Swamiji Maharaj Bagh is in Dayalbah, Agra. Its a very nice place designed and looks very great.

title: Big Name little Glory
review: It is called the Father of Tajmahal by Indians which is anything but true, it is a good work but nothing great, there are better paces carved and inlaid, unless you don't have too much time dont waste your time.
